<h3><a name="controls">Icons and Controls</a></h3>
<hr />
  Throughout the site, you will see these icons next to entries. <br />
  <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-info-sign btn btn-info"></span> This icon is used to <b>view</b> an item. <br />
  <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-edit btn btn-warning"></span> This icon is used to <b>edit</b> an item. <br />
  <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-remove-sign btn btn-danger"></span> This icon is used to <b>delete</b> an item. <br />
  <a href="#top">Top</a>
<br /><br />

<h3><a name="users">Managing Users</a></h3>
<hr />
<p>
  The system comes with a default username of <b>admin@admin.com</b> and
  default password of <b>admin123</b>. You should <a style="color: red; font-weight: bold;" href="/users">
 change the password </a> before you do anything else.
  You can add as many users as you need under <b>Manage</b> > <b>Users</b> in the sidebar menu.
</p>
<p>
  After creating a user, a confirmation email will be sent to the email address used to create the account.
  You need to click the link in email to activiate the acount before you can use it.
</p>
<p>
  If you delete all of the users, you will be locked out of the system.
</p>
  <a href="#top">Top</a>
<br /><br />

<h3><a name="settings">Enter Settings</a></h3>
<hr />
<p>
  After changing the default password, you will need to enter your company informaion under <b><a href="/settings">Settings</a>.</b>
</p>
<p>
  The email will be used as the contact email address if you choose to email your invoices, so make sure it is valid.
</p>
<p>
  You can optionally add an image that will be placed in the upper right hand corner of your invoices.  It should be fairly small.
</p>
  <a href="#top">Top</a>
<br /><br />

<h3><a name="clients">Adding Clients</a></h3>
<hr />
<p>
  You can now start adding your clients under <b><a href="/clients/new">Manage > Clients > New</a></b> in the sidebar.
  This information will be used to later when you start entering in jobs.
  You'll need to enter the client name, a contact name or something like "Accounting Department", a mailing address, and optionally an email address
  if you want to be able to email the client the invoice.
</p>
  <a href="#top">Top</a>
<br /><br />

<h3><a name="jobtypes">Adding Job Types</a></h3>
<hr />
<p>
  Next, you'll need to add job types under <b><a href="/jobtypes/new">Manage > Jobtypes > New</a></b> in the sidebar.
  This might be something like "In-Town Bicycle", "Vehichle", "Service of Process", or what ever you classify your delivery types as.
  You can add as many job types as you need.
</p>
  <a href="#top">Top</a>
<br /><br />

<h3><a name="servicetypes">Adding Service Types</a></h3>
<hr />
<p>
  You can add service types under <b><a href="/service/new">Manage > Service Types > New</a></b>.
  A service type might be "ASAP", "Rush", "Regular", ect.  Again, you can add as many service types as you need.
</p>
  <a href="#top">Top</a>
<br /><br />

<h3><a name="jobs">Adding Jobs</a></h3>
<hr />
<p>
  You can now start adding jobs under <b><a href="/jobs/new">Jobs > New</a></b> in the sidebar.  Clients, Job Types, and Service Types
  are all now available for fast data entry.
</p>
<p>
  Start by selecting the <b>date</b> that the job was done.  The date picker defaults to todays date, but can be set to any date.
</p>
<p>
  Select the <b>client</b> from the drop down menu.  You can use the keyboard to select clients quickly, as well.  If a client is not in the list, you can click
  the <b><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-plus-sign"></span></b> icon to add a new client.
</p>
<p>
  You can enter a <b>billing reference</b> for the job if you use them.
</p>
<p>
  <b>Caller, Job Type, Description, Zone, Service Type, and Total</b> are all required to be filled in.  The
  <b>Details</b> field is for any extra notes about the job.  You can add things like wait time, weight, or
  anything else you like.  Any dollar amounts entered here <b>will not</b> be automatically added to the total.
  You'll need add any extra charges into the final total of the job.
</p>
<p>
  After you hit the <b>Submit</b> button, you can continue to add jobs, edit those jobs,
  or delete them. You can see an example job below.
</p>
